      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2021-03-19T12:28:43.567Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Yeah Kickr bike only supports slope mode.</p>\n<p>Regarding optimum shifting, I am not sure about that one, Zwift operates in slope mode so if you have to shift a lot in Zwift then the likelyhood is our resistance mode might be better as it is just a fixed resistance.  We have no control over shifting in either mode I don\u2019t think.  The initial gear you start in might affect it but I don\u2019t have much knowlege on this.  You can do exactly what you want no in our app, you just have to click the free-ride switch before starting your intervals or keep it in free ride the whole time.</p>\n<p>Let me know how it goes.</p>",
