      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/57b2e6/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2021-03-19T13:34:15.503Z",
      "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-English\" data-username=\"Alex\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"534\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/48/1331_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Alex:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You can do exactly what you want no in our app, you just have to click the free-ride switch before starting your intervals or keep it in free ride the whole time.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Sort of\u2026<br>\nIn Free-Ride and with the resistance adjustment at 10%, you can fairly quickly change from a relatively low to a relatively high resistance. But you need to \u201cfast-trigger\u201d the resistance button a couple times.<br>\nThe ideal situation would be to do the recovery intervals in ERG mode while in a low enough gear to not hit the Power Floor of your trainer and do the work intervals (sprints) in a maximal resistance setting. It would be nice to have the app do the switching. Depending on your trainer, you might just have to change small/big chainring or a couple shifts in the rear, or maybe just nothing to change.</p>",
