      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/ecb155/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2021-04-10T11:53:46.433Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I\u2019ll try to explain in other words:<br>\nI have set the increments for resistance change to 1%.  Increasing (and waiting a few seconds) did not seem to change anything from about 15 to 29%.  Going from 29% to 30% gave me a jump of about 70Watts.<br>\nI wonder if this is due to how Wahoo handles resistance.  I think in the wahoo app there are only 5% increments in resistance mode.</p>\n<p>Anyway going back to the opening post:  I think CURVE or SIM/SLOPE mode feel a lot closer to actually riding a bike in the wild <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/wink.png?v=9\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\">  And to be able to preset those for intervals would be great, imho.<br>\nHope you can make it happen <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"></p>",
