      "created_at": "2021-04-10T12:17:59.379Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I\u2019ll test again on my next workout- perhaps it was just a one time hiccup?!</p>\n<p>It\u2019s kind of hard to tell with a touch device, if the input actually worked- especially if you have lactate in your eyeballs <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/sweat_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":sweat_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":sweat_smile:\"></p>\n<p>I usually turn off \u201ceverything that beeps\u201d on my bike computer, but perhaps it\u2019s possible to get some kind of aural feedback if a command sent to the trainer has actually been received?  Also:  I find the number for the level/increments a bit small even on the iPad.  Seems too me the app could use a bit more of that screen-real estate, there is a lot of space around the numbers</p>",
